race.comment: ROSE DIAMOND (11) consistent mare who finds her race third-up despite drawing out. Stalked the speed from the awkward draw when a courageous fourth over 1400m at the Sapphire Coast. Placed at the trip and should prove too good for these. SOLAR ORBIT (7) returned from a lengthy break with a plugging sixth over 1300m at Canberra. Ready to jump out in distance and gets his chance with the weight relief. Each way. THE BUS (8) gripped on late from the awkward gate when sent forward before finishing fifth over 1400m at the Sapphire Coast. Well-placed and expected to feature. KERMANDO (1) drifted back early at his second run back when a disappointing eighth over 1460m at Queanbeyan. Blinkers stay on and look for him working home late. AIN'T SEEN MARS (9) far from disgraced on debut and gives the impression he's looking for this trip and further now.
